 254:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      The compilation flag USE_HAL_I2C_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
 255:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
 256:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      Use Functions HAL_I2C_RegisterCallback() or HAL_I2C_RegisterAddrCallback()
 257:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      to register an interrupt callback.
 258:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****     [..]
 259:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      Function HAL_I2C_RegisterCallback() allows to register following callbacks:
 260:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MasterTxCpltCallback : callback for Master transmission end of transfer.
 261:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MasterRxCpltCallback : callback for Master reception end of transfer.
 262:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) SlaveTxCpltCallback  : callback for Slave transmission end of transfer.
 263:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) SlaveRxCpltCallback  : callback for Slave reception end of transfer.
 264:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) ListenCpltCallback   : callback for end of listen mode.
 265:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MemTxCpltCallback    : callback for Memory transmission end of transfer.
 266:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MemRxCpltCallback    : callback for Memory reception end of transfer.
 267:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) ErrorCallback        : callback for error detection.
 268:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) AbortCpltCallback    : callback for abort completion process.
 269:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MspInitCallback      : callback for Msp Init.
 270:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MspDeInitCallback    : callback for Msp DeInit.
 271:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 272:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      and a pointer to the user callback function.
 273:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****     [..]
 274:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      For specific callback AddrCallback use dedicated register callbacks : HAL_I2C_RegisterAddrCall
 275:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****     [..]
 276:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      Use function HAL_I2C_UnRegisterCallback to reset a callback to the default
 277:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      weak function.
 278:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      HAL_I2C_UnRegisterCallback takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
 279:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      and the Callback ID.
 280:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      This function allows to reset following callbacks:
 281:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MasterTxCpltCallback : callback for Master transmission end of transfer.
 282:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MasterRxCpltCallback : callback for Master reception end of transfer.
 283:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) SlaveTxCpltCallback  : callback for Slave transmission end of transfer.
 284:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) SlaveRxCpltCallback  : callback for Slave reception end of transfer.
 285:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) ListenCpltCallback   : callback for end of listen mode.
 286:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MemTxCpltCallback    : callback for Memory transmission end of transfer.
 287:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MemRxCpltCallback    : callback for Memory reception end of transfer.
 288:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) ErrorCallback        : callback for error detection.
 289:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) AbortCpltCallback    : callback for abort completion process.
 290:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MspInitCallback      : callback for Msp Init.
 291:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****        (+) MspDeInitCallback    : callback for Msp DeInit.
 292:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****     [..]
 293:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      For callback AddrCallback use dedicated register callbacks : HAL_I2C_UnRegisterAddrCallback().
 294:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****     [..]
 295:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      By default, after the HAL_I2C_Init() and when the state is HAL_I2C_STATE_RESET
 296:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions:
 297:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      examples HAL_I2C_MasterTxCpltCallback(), HAL_I2C_MasterRxCpltCallback().
 298:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are
 299:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      reset to the legacy weak functions in the HAL_I2C_Init()/ HAL_I2C_DeInit() only when
 300:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 301:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      If MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_I2C_Init()/ HAL_I2C_DeInit()
 302:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand) whatever the state.
 303:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****     [..]
 304:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_I2C_STATE_READY state only.
 305:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit functions that can be registered/unregistered
 306:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      in HAL_I2C_STATE_READY or HAL_I2C_STATE_RESET state,
 307:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 308:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      Then, the user first registers the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 309:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      using HAL_I2C_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_I2C_DeInit()
 310:../Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_i2c.c ****      or HAL_I2C_Init() function.
